text: Christine Gaskell (born 1957) is a female British former swimmer. ==Swimming career== Gaskell represented England and won a gold medal in the 100 breaststroke event, at the 1974 British Commonwealth Games in Christchurch, New Zealand. She also participated in the 200 metres breaststroke and medley relay. She swam for the Rochdale Swimming Club and first gained international selection in 1972. ==References== Category:1957 births Category:Living people Category:British female swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 1974 British Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in swimming Category:Commonwealth Games gold medallists for England
